{
  "texts": [
    "To evaluate the model's response given a prompt and its rubric, we prompt an off-the-shelf LLM to judge whether the response satisfies each rubric separately for its simplicity and reproducibility.",
    "Specifically, we choose o3-mini as our rubric verifier for its strong reasoning ability and cost efficiency.",
    "The prompt template is provided in Section B.",
    "For each prompt, the model receives a binary label (TRUE or False) for whether it satisfies all criteria, and we report the percentage of responses with TRUE label for each category of instructions, including ComplexIF (CIF), Carried Context (CC), and System Steerability (SS).",
    "We report the performance of several frontier LLMs, including GPT-series models (Achiam et al., 2023), Gemini-series models (Huang and Yang, 2025), Claude 4 Sonnet (Anthropic, 2024)."
  ]
}